### Rmd purposes

**Aim and context:** This file is used to subset the ABARES NLUM dataset into relevant agricultural commodities and to plot their extent across Australia.

**Analysis:**
- Subset ABARES categories to agricultural cells at native 250m^2^ resolution
- Aggregate raster to 10 arc-min (\~324 km^2^) cells
- Apply a 10% floor

<!--
NOTE (review, 2026-07-03): the plan above describes a MEAN aggregation to get a
0-1 proportion of agricultural land per output cell, followed by a 10% floor.
The code actually implements a MODAL aggregation (dominant land-use class per
cell), and no floor is applied anywhere. These are genuinely different outputs:

  - modal  -> "what is the single most common category in this cell?"
  - mean of a presence/absence layer -> "what fraction of this cell is
    covered by host habitat?", which a floor can then filter on

Modal aggregation with na.rm = TRUE also means a cell can be assigned a host
category even if only a tiny handful of the ~5,000 underlying 250 m pixels in
that cell belong to it (since NA pixels are excluded before the mode is
taken) - so sparse, scattered occurrences can end up rendered as fully solid
~18 km cells. If a density/coverage map is what's intended, consider building
a per-category binary presence raster, aggregating that with fun = "mean" to
get proportion cover, and thresholding at 0.1 - rather than aggregating the
categorical raster directly. Left the modal approach in place below since
this is a design decision, not a bug, but flagging it clearly since it's a
mismatch with the stated method.
-->

